Oct 15 2007 	Better than expected	After reading the reviews on this place I was wondering what I had let myself in for. Bed bugs, dirt, shabby, dirty towels, toilets that did not work etc... No need to worry however, I found this place to be clean, rooms anyway, corridors not, clean towels provided every day, and although I did have a problem with the toilet it was fixed quickly by the hotel. Reception very helpful and efficient.No it not the Ritz, but if you are looking for somewhere that is very reasonably priced with a very good location then this is it. We had 3 rooms, all were large and everything worked in all of them. The beds and bathrooms were clean. Yes it could do with updating, but overall I feel that it was good value for money. The location was great. A short walk to Fisherman's wharf, and if you turn right out of the hotel and climb the hill, you come across Polk St. Turn right into this and you will find great bars and places to eat. We sat outside a bar and met some very nice people who live in the area. We were welcomed back here more than once. I have stayed in hotels with far worse service than this, and noisier, which were meant to be higher 'star'. Don't expect it to be fantastic - you get what you pay for, but rooms are clean, and the location could not have been better.	
