Dec 12 2006 	A fine hotel for the price	We booked this hotel because of location and price. It was in an excellent location and had free covered parking. We could walk to Fisherman's Wharf every day in about 15 minutes. It was in a very safe part of town, we never felt uncomfortable walking everywhere. The staff was helpful...they even put us in a suite the first couple nights even though we booked a standard room because that's all they had left when we showed up. However, the rooms are definitely &quot;economy&quot;. Don't go expecting the Hilton and you won't be disappointed. Everything was clean and both rooms that we stayed in had plenty of room and all the amenities you need on vacation. It was nothing special, but it also was not bad. All we cared about was a good location and cleanliness and we got both.	
