Jul 17 2006	Don't expect much...	I live in San Francisco, and when a family member told me she had booked here I was a bit wary- but I knew that she was on a budget and I had never actually heard anything bad about the place The hotel is in a safe, if uninteresting neighborhood and from the outside looks like any number of other inexpensive. boxy hotels built for people who want something better than a 'motel' but can't afford to stay in a good chain hotel or nearer to the center of things. Perhaps a bit larger than most. I figured that it would be fine for a few nights. I was wrong.The lobby is nice enough, but we first began to have doubts on the way up to the room. The place is built around a central courtyard (pool area), with most doors opening directly onto the courtyard or exposed corridors (like a motel), and pretty much everything needed a fresh paint job. The carpets were worn in the corridors, and some walls were patched and painted over. Overall it looked like a cheap motel on a freeway anywhere in America- but bigger (4 or 5 floors). Still, all she wanted was a clean, servicable room for a few nights in town and we didn't expect the Ritz Carlton anyway .It was when we opened the door of the room that my heart sank. The room absolutely stank of disinfectant and odd smells- I mean it was overpowering! Unusable! No kidding! There was a dirty towel thrown in the bathtub, and a dirty comforter on the bed. The carpet was worn, the walls were painted concrete, and the baseboard heater cover was falling off. It was a truly depressing room to begin with, and the smell made it just not possible to stay there.I called the desk and explained the problem without jumping down their throats. They told us they were booked solid, and suggested we open the window. Sorry, nothing more to be done. Quite polite and absolutely unhelpful. Since it was booked through ----, we called them and explained the situation. I gotta give them credit, they really jumped through hoops to find her another place to stay. At one point they had three people working on it, and eventually found her another place nearby. They even ate the 'cancelation fee' (a one-night charge) this place refused to waive.So there we are- maybe we just got a bad room, but I doubt it. This place claims to have been renovated on 2003 but it certainly doesn't look like it. I didn't expect much, but I expected much better than this. Consider this review fair warning- and absolutely honest and aboveboard, I would much rather not have taken the time to write this!	
